author: @madhavpr
text: Good morning Krish. Very nicely summarized.  Gen AI is a a family of tools with its strength and limitations. Just like you can't use a rocket launcher for killing a mosquito, you can't use generative AI for every use case. Secondly, as data scientists, I feel that our primary objective is to make sense of data and how to interpret the results properly. So irrespective of whatever algorithms we use, we need to find out if the results make sense or not. (of course, we also need to know the ins and outs of the algorithms too)
